The paper deals with the problem of approximate nearest neighbor search, which is a fundamental problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of random forests and random projection trees, which are popular in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the use of multi-label classifiers, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
